  "texts": [
    "An example of this is visible in the ATIS dataset, where minority classes atis flight no and atis flight time are similar to the majority class atis flight, leading to biased predictions in favor of the majority trained class, resulting in poor performance in both minority classes, as seen in table 3.",
    "This phenomenon is not observed in few-shot learning approaches due to the absence of a biased training process.",
    "Our hypothesis suggests that those divergences arise from the distinct representations and interpretations of classes by each model: in encoder-only models, classes are mere positions in the output vector, with the last layer weights dictating sentence-to-class mapping without considering the class name, leading to a probability vector solely based on the input sentence; in contrast, decoder-only models represent classes by their names and semantics, potentially causing collisions among classes with similar names.The Zero-Shot LLaMA2 consistently exhibits suboptimal performance compared to other approaches.",
    "Yet paradoxically achieves high scores in the majority class.",
    "This is not due to its larger cardinality but rather because the class name, atis flight, is the most generalizable, being present in 67% of the utterances."
  ],
